name: atlas_img_1939
description: This map service features scanned, georeferenced historical aerial photography collected in May of 1939. The scanned images are panchromatic (black and white) and have a spatial resolution of approximately 4 feet. While the original prints are archived by the Rhode Island Statewide Planning Program, the scanned images are available from the Rhode Island Geographic Information System (RIGIS) consortium (http://www.edc.uri.edu/rigis).
serviceDescription:
This map service features scanned, georeferenced historical aerial photography collected in May of 1939.  The scanned images are panchromatic (black and white) and have a spatial resolution of approximately 4 feet.  While the original prints are archived by the Rhode Island Statewide Planning Program, the scanned images are available from the Rhode Island Geographic Information System (RIGIS) consortium (http://www.edc.uri.edu/rigis).

This map service is published by the University of Rhode Island Environmental Data Center as part of its Rhode Island Digital Atlas initiative (http://www.edc.uri.edu/atlas). Please review the terms and conditions associated with this map service at http://www.edc.uri.edu/atlas/about/terms.html before accessing and/or using this service.
